  <original-body>The test_helper.rb file generated for a plugin does not run the plugin's tests on 'rake test' (standing in the plugin's directory). That is very easy to verify:

* ./script/generate plugin my_plugin
* cd vendor/plugins/my_plugin
* rake test

No tests will be run. A &quot;truth test&quot; is generated by default so you should see (&quot;1 tests, 1 assertions, 0 failures, 0 errors&quot;). That's because test/unit is not required in the test_helper.rb file and the fix is just that, require it (see attached patch).</original-body>
